Recently, the Inclined Bicep Curl started to gain a lot of popularity. This leads to the question, is it actually good and should you be doing it? Well the Inclined Curl actually targets the long head of the bicep, so it makes up a lot of that outer fullness of the bicep. And what makes it different from a standard bicep curl is essentially the range of motion. In this upwards position, your arms are down to your side and actually limits the amount of stretch that you're able to get on the long head of the bicep. Doing an Inclined Curl allows that arm to come back behind the body to get a full stretch on the long head. This is an amazing exercise to tear down those muscle fibers and build big biceps.
